text: Taylor Elizabeth Louderman (born December 21, 1990) is an American actress, singer and dancer. She is best known for the role of Regina George in the Broadway musical Mean Girls. She was nominated for the Tony Award for Best Actress in a Musical in 2018 for her role in Mean Girls. She is also a voice actress who voices Blair in the Nick Jr. series Sunny Day.
